        <section>
            <h2>Bharathanatyam: The Geometric Grace</h2>
            <p>Originating from the sacred temples of Tamil Nadu, Bharatanatyam is a celestial blend of fire and geometry. It is defined by the Araimandi (half-squat) posture, where the dancer’s body creates sharp, architectural lines and intricate rhythmic patterns. This art form is a "Visual Yoga" that balances Nritta (pure, technical movement) with Abhinaya (expressive storytelling), turning every flick of the wrist and glance of the eye into a profound spiritual conversation.</p>
