            <h2>Kathak:The Art of the Storyteller</h2>
            <p>Born from the nomadic bards of North India, Kathak is the mesmerizing art of the "Katha" or story. It is a dance of breathtaking transitions—moving from subtle, delicate eyebrow movements to thunderous, lightning-fast footwork and dizzying pirouettes known as Chakkars. Historically evolving from temple courtyards to the grand Mughal palaces, it remains a vibrant dialogue between the dancer and the percussionist, where rhythm itself becomes a narrative.</p>
