            <h2>Kathakali: The Theater of Gods and Demons</h2>
            <p>Hailing from the lush landscapes of Kerala, Kathakali is a majestic "Story-Play" that blurs the line between dance and drama. It is instantly recognized by its otherworldly, elaborate costumes and heavy "Pacha" (green) or "Kathi" (knife) makeup that transforms humans into deities and demons. Without uttering a single word, the performer uses a sophisticated language of 24 hand gestures and incredible eye-muscle control to enact epic battles from the Ramayana and Mahabharata.</p>
